==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Were
<hw>Were</hw> <pr>(w⟦emac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>wer</ets>; akin to OS. & OHG. <ets>wer</ets>, Goth.
<ets>wa⟦iacute⟧r</ets>, L. <ets>vir</ets>, Skr. <ets>v⟦imac⟧ra</ets>.
Cf. <er>Weregild</er>, and <er>Werewolf</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A man.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A fine for slaying a man; the money value set upon a
man's life; weregild.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Every man was valued at a certain sum, which was called his
<qex>were</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bosworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weregild</ent>⟦br⟧
